
@startuml

' Define classes
class Student {
    +String studentID
    +String name
    +List<Course> registeredCourses
}

class TeachingAssistant {
    +String taID
    +String name
    +List<Course> assignedCourses
}

class Course {
    +String courseCode
    +String title
    +List<TeachingAssistant> tas
    +List<Student> students
}

class Appointment {
    +String appointmentID
    +DateTime time
    +Course course
    +TeachingAssistant ta
    +Student student
}

' Relationships
Student "1" -- "0..*" Course : registers for
Course "1" -- "0..*" TeachingAssistant : has
Course "1" -- "0..*" Student : enrolled by
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Course : assigned to
Appointment "1" -- "1" Student : requested by
Appointment "1" -- "1" TeachingAssistant : provided by
Appointment "1" -- "1" Course : related to

@enduml

### Explanation of Key Elements:
- **Student**: Can register for multiple courses and can make appointments only with TAs of those courses.
- **TeachingAssistant (TA)**: Assigned to one or more courses and can provide help only for those courses.
- **Course**: Has a list of students and TAs. An appointment is always associated with one specific course.
- **Appointment**: Links a student, a TA, and a course together for a scheduled meeting.

